  "text": "Evidence for a steady-state flux in actin filaments came from the time-course of the equilibration of labeled actin monomers THE JOURNAL Or CELL BIOLOGY \" VOLUME 88 MARCH 1981 654-659 C The Rockefeller University Press \" 0021-9525/81/03/0654/06 $1 .00 with fully polymerized actin [CITATION_1] . Treadmilling in microtubules was first suggested by the kinetics of labeled monomer incorporation into a steady-state sample of microtubules [CITATION_2] . Another way to evaluate the steady-state flux is to measure the reaction rate constants at the two ends directly as Bergen and Borisy (3) have done for microtubules.",
